{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkNbNqBeX95VqAYfmmj2q8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package evolution\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"context\"\n     5→\t\"fmt\"\n     6→\t\"os\"\n     7→\t\"path/filepath\"\n     8→\t\"regexp\"\n     9→\t\"strings\"\n    10→)\n    11→\n    12→// Curator merges lessons into prompt files using ACE-style curation.\n    13→type Curator struct {\n    14→\tLLM   LLMClient\n    15→\tAudit *AuditLogger\n    16→}\n    17→\n    18→// lessonAlreadyPresent checks whether the lesson's key insight or action is\n    19→// already present in the current prompt text (case-insensitive substring match).\n    20→func lessonAlreadyPresent(currentPrompt string, lesson *Lesson) bool {\n    21→\tlower := strings.ToLower(currentPrompt)\n    22→\tif lesson.Insight != \"\" && strings.Contains(lower, strings.ToLower(lesson.Insight)) {\n    23→\t\treturn true\n    24→\t}\n    25→\tif lesson.SuggestedAction != \"\" && strings.Contains(lower, strings.ToLower(lesson.SuggestedAction)) {\n    26→\t\treturn true\n    27→\t}\n    28→\treturn false\n    29→}\n    30→\n    31→// ErrSanityCheckFailed indicates the curated content failed the prompt sanity check.\n    32→var ErrSanityCheckFailed = fmt.Errorf(\"curation output failed sanity check\")\n    33→\n    34→// Curate performs core curation logic: reads the current prompt, calls the LLM to\n    35→// merge the lesson, and returns the updated prompt content as a string. All corruption\n    36→// safeguards (conversational guard, code-fence stripping, sanity check) are applied.\n    37→// Returns (\"\", nil) when the lesson is already present and no update is needed.\n    38→// Returns (\"\", ErrSanityCheckFailed) when the curated output fails the sanity check.\n    39→func (c *Curator) Curate(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, lesson *Lesson) (string, error) {\n    40→\ttargetPath := filepath.Join(projectDir, lesson.Target)\n    41→\tcurrent, err := os.